OSOGBO. – No fewer than 10,000 athletes will take part in the first Osun Heritage International Half Marathon Race on November 23rd, 2019. The race was part of the activities lined up to mark the first year of the administration of Governor Adegboyega Oyetola in office. The State Director of Sports, Layi Adesiyan, disclosed this while speaking with newsmen in Osogbo. The programme is being organised by Osun State Government in conjunction with some technical experts in the field of sports. He said that an inter-ministerial committee had been put in place to midwife the event. The Director of the half marathon race, Mr Aderemi Akinwale also said that the 21 km race was scheduled to take off from Government secretariat Abere through the bypass and terminate at the Osogbo Sport City Stadium.